  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">OGB PA Discretionary Contribution to Nigeria FY2018-2019</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The amount of the discretionary fund will be spent on programmes and the balance will be spent on core costs. The amount going to programme will be added to ONL DF and spent on 3 local partners that are NAWIA, CCDP and YMCA.  Oxfam in Nigeria has 3 local partners in the middle belt of Nigeria in Benue, Nasarawa and Plateau. They have implemented the Village Savings and Loan Associations (VSLA) projects funded 100% through unrestricted lines (counterpart) thus far. There is no donor funding involved. They submitted their annual work plan and budget early this fiscal year for the continuation of the project. These three local partners are: 1. NAWIA: the Nigeria Association of Women in Agriculture in Benue 2. CCDP: Cocin Community Development Program in Plateau 3. YMCA: Young (wo)Men&apos;s  Christian Association in Narasawa   Together, they have been reaching the past two years 42,702 farmers, 75% of whom are females. Together, they raised $1,800,000 to build start -ups, small (agro allied) businesses and downright farming activities. The plan for April 2018 - March 2019 was to add 22,000 more farmers this fiscal year.</narrative>
  </description>
